The paper deals with auction mechanisms, which are a central topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The focus on individual rationality, Pareto optimality, and incentive compatibility suggests a connection to mechanism design (cs.GT, cs.EC). The use of budget limits and the distinction between divisible and indivisible items suggest a connection to combinatorial auctions (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.IT).
